The governor of Kaduna State, Nasir El-rufai has disclosed that the State will be on lockdown again if the people fail to observe COVID-19 rules. El-rufai disclosed this on Twitter while responding to a tweet that the Governor should not lockdown the State. There has been a spike in COVID-19 cases across the country, which government has declared a second wave of the virus. The Presidential Task Force (PTF) has advised State to close down bars, clubs, restaurants and other activities. “We will only lock Kaduna State down if the public health protocols are not observed or complied with by our citizens. “PLEASE Wear masks! Avoid crowds! Social-distance! Wash hands! @elrufai,” he stated.